  <summary>4/16/1997--Introduced.
Smoke-Free Transportation Facilities Act of 1997 - Directs the Secretary of Transportation to require, as a condition of Federal financial assistance, that the owner or operator of a transportation facility take the necessary action to prohibit smoking in any indoor portion of the facility accessible to the general public.</summary>
